inclusion.criterion: On the day of ET, patients will be randomized according to a computer-generated randomization
inclusion.label: met

inclusion.criterion: A maximum of two good quality embryos are to be replaced.
inclusion.label: met

inclusion.criterion: Patients are asked to keep a mildly full bladder so that the uterus can be visualized by abdominal sonogram during the procedure.
inclusion.label: met

inclusion.criterion: A bivalve speculum is inserted into the vagina and the cervix is cleaned with warm saline and culture medium.
inclusion.label: met

inclusion.criterion: The axis, degree of flexion and the configuration of the uterine cavity are determined by transabdominal ultrasound examination before the transfer.
inclusion.label: met

inclusion.criterion: Under transabdominal ultrasound guidance, the outer catheter is inserted into the cervical canal 4 cm from the external os, with the tip just beyond the internal os.
inclusion.label: met

inclusion.criterion: The inner transfer catheter with the loaded embryo(s) is then inserted into the uterine cavity via the outer cannula.
inclusion.label: met

inclusion.criterion: The luteal phase support will be used if needed and antenatal management is as usual, if pregnant.
inclusion.label: met

inclusion.criterion: Sample size estimation The ongoing pregnancy rate of IVF-ET in 2010 was about 30.0%.
inclusion.label: unknown

inclusion.criterion: (i) ET in the fresh cycle (ii) Age <43 year (iii) Normal uterine cavity shown on ultrasound scanning
inclusion.label: met

exclusion.criterion: Presence of hydrosalpinx on pelvic scanning
exclusion.label: triggers

exclusion.criterion: Previously joined in the same study
exclusion.label: unknown

notes: Patient has a history of BPH with multiple urological procedures, including suprapubic prostatectomy. He had severe urethral stricture requiring surgical intervention.
